# Citations for the 8 AcuGuide Hand/Wrist Points

Each point lists **Location** sources (where the point is) and **Evidence** sources (clinical research, where it exists). Evidence strength is noted honestly: most hand points are traditional/low-evidence; **PC6 is the exception** with strong research.

All 8 points are pregnancy-safe (LI4 intentionally excluded).

---

### 1. TE3 — Zhongzhu (中渚) · *tension/temporal headache, neck-shoulder*
**Location**
- Acupoints.org — https://www.acupoints.org/te3-acupuncture-point/
- Master Tung / eLotus CORE — https://www.mastertungacupuncture.org/acupuncture/traditional/points/th3
- Acupuncture Nepal — https://acupuncturenepal.com/zhongzhu-te3.html
- Yin Yang House — https://yinyanghouse.com/theory/acupuncturepoints/th3/

**Evidence** — *Traditional indication for headache; no point-specific trial. General context:*
- Acupuncture for tension-type headache, systematic review & network meta-analysis — https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC10325685/

